g the placeholder; it seems like the right call is to keep it for now. However, there’s this status that includes metadata related to `org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18`, which might indicate an untracked directory with generated metadata. I need to think through how this affects our overall setup and whether we’ll actually need that metadata or if it can be safely ignored. It feels a bit confusing, but I want to ensure everything stays organized!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for `ResourceBundleViewResolver`.\n\nAdded:\n\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_webmvc/ResourceBundleViewResolverTest.java`\n  - Public dedicated test class for the active dynamic-access class.\n  - Exercises `ResourceBundleViewResolver.resolveViewName(...)` through normal public API.\n  - Reaches `ResourceBundle.getBundle(String, Locale, ClassLoader)` via the resolver’s resource-bundle loading path.\n  - Verifies the resolved `InternalResourceView` and configured URL.\n\n- `tests/src/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/src/test/resources/org_springframework/spring_webmvc/resource_bundle_views.properties`\n  - Classpath resource bundle used by the resolver.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction. Note: `git status` also shows an unrelated untracked `metadata/org.springframework/spring-webmvc/5.3.18/` directory that I did not modify.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03c95e5e1db1cf34016a264b34d03481959f6a1ef65f2f9845\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 405, "output": 728, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24173, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780894499723, "responseId": "resp_03c95e5e1db1cf34016a264b2448508195b55cc0686ebe50a5"}, "toolResults": []}
